{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "OBJ_STATE/bonesfromcurve", "tags": "character"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Bones from Curve"], "extent": [50, 71]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Allows you to create a bone chain along a curve."], "extent": [71, 128]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [128, 143], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This tool is useful for creating a character\u2019s spine or tail, as it evenly spaces bones on a curve. It could also be used to form the skeleton of a snake."], "extent": [143, 300]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": "includeme", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Using Bones"], "extent": [300, 330], "body": [{"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["In the viewport, press ", {"keys": ["Tab"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " and type ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/obj/path", "type": "link", "text": ["Path"], "fullpath": "/nodes/obj/path"}, "."], "extent": [330, 404]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Draw the curve in the viewport."], "extent": [404, 447]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Make sure the curve is selected, and click the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "OBJ_STATE/bonesfromcurve", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/OBJ_STATE/bonesfromcurve"}, "Bones from Curve tool on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Characters"]}, " tab."], "extent": [447, 585], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["You can change the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Kinematics"]}, " to Follow Curve in the drop-down menu on the operations toolbar if you want the bones to be bound to the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/curve", "type": "link", "text": ["curve"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/curve"}, ". This allows you to modify the curve and the bone chain is automatically adjusted."], "extent": [585, 843]}],